{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":691,"text":"Whenever I get to travel for work,"},{"time":2794,"text":"I try to find out where my\ndrinking water comes from,"},{"time":5326,"text":"and where my poop and pee go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7017,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":8885,"text":"This has earned me the nickname\n\"The Poo Princess\" in my family,"},{"time":11936,"text":"and it's ruined many family vacations,\nbecause this is not normal."},{"time":16612,"text":"But thinking about where it all goes\nis the first step in activating"},{"time":21897,"text":"what are actually superpowers\nin our poop and pee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24736,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":25836,"text":"Yeah."},{"time":27014,"text":"And if we use them well,"},{"time":28196,"text":"we can live healthier\nand more beautifully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30371,"text":"Check out this landscape\nin Santa Fe, New Mexico."},{"time":34771,"text":"Just notice what kinds of words\nand feelings come to mind."},{"time":39588,"text":"This landscape was watered\nwith treated sewage water."},{"time":43892,"text":"Does that change anything for you?"},{"time":46458,"text":"I imagine it might."},{"time":50191,"text":"And that's OK."},{"time":52897,"text":"How we feel about this"},{"time":55118,"text":"is going to determine exactly\nhow innovative we can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58589,"text":"And I want to explain how it works,"},{"time":62675,"text":"but what words do I use?"},{"time":65471,"text":"I mean, I can use profane words\nlike \"shit\" and \"piss,\""},{"time":69147,"text":"and then my grandma won't watch the video."},{"time":71451,"text":"Or I can use childish words\nlike \"poo\" and \"pee.\" Eh."},{"time":75252,"text":"Or I can use scientific words\nlike \"excrement\" and \"feces.\" Humph."},{"time":79994,"text":"I'll use a mix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81285,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":82649,"text":"It's all I got. (Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85678,"text":"So, in this suburb,"},{"time":87195,"text":"the poo and the pee and the wash water\nare going to this treatment plant"},{"time":91144,"text":"right in the middle of the community."},{"time":93285,"text":"It looks more like a park\nthan a treatment plant."},{"time":95970,"text":"The poo at the very bottom\nof all those layers of gravel --"},{"time":99380,"text":"not touching anyone --"},{"time":100920,"text":"is providing solid food\nfor those marsh plants."},{"time":104238,"text":"And the clean, clear water\nthat comes out the other end"},{"time":107543,"text":"is traveling underground\nto water each person's yard."},{"time":111328,"text":"So even though they're in a desert,"},{"time":113047,"text":"they get their own personal oasis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115963,"text":"This approach is called\nIntegrated Water Management,"},{"time":119199,"text":"or holistic or closed-loop."},{"time":122071,"text":"Whatever you want to call it,"},{"time":123612,"text":"it's in conflict with the status quo\nof how we think about sanitation,"},{"time":127271,"text":"which is contain, treat, push it away."},{"time":131239,"text":"But in this approach,\nwe're doing one step better."},{"time":133609,"text":"We're designing for reuse\nfrom the very beginning,"},{"time":135995,"text":"because everything does get reused,"},{"time":138587,"text":"only now we're planning for it."},{"time":140765,"text":"And often, that makes for\nreally beautiful spaces."},{"time":145042,"text":"But the most important thing\nabout this system"},{"time":149131,"text":"isn't the technicals of how it works."},{"time":151812,"text":"It's how you feel about it."},{"time":154002,"text":"Do you want this in your yard?"},{"time":156507,"text":"Why not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158368,"text":"I got really curious about this question."},{"time":161111,"text":"Why don't we see more\ninnovation in sanitation?"},{"time":164475,"text":"Why isn't that kind of thing\nthe new normal?"},{"time":167610,"text":"And I care so much about this question,"},{"time":169814,"text":"that I work for a nonprofit called Recode."},{"time":171997,"text":"We want to accelerate adoption"},{"time":173925,"text":"of sustainable building\nand development practices."},{"time":176721,"text":"We want more innovation."},{"time":180274,"text":"But a lot of times,\nwhole categories of innovation --"},{"time":183375,"text":"ones that can help us\nlive more beautifully --"},{"time":186197,"text":"turn out to be illegal."},{"time":188728,"text":"Today's regulations and codes\nwere written under the assumption"},{"time":192204,"text":"that best practices\nwould remain best practices,"},{"time":196242,"text":"with incremental updates forever and ever."},{"time":199387,"text":"But innovation isn't always incremental."},{"time":202285,"text":"It turns out, how we feel\nabout any particular new technique"},{"time":205790,"text":"gets into everything we do:"},{"time":207663,"text":"how we talk about it,"},{"time":208957,"text":"how we encourage people to study,"},{"time":210807,"text":"our jokes, our codes ..."},{"time":212754,"text":"And it ultimately determines\nhow innovative we can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216503,"text":"So, that's the first reason\nwe don't innovate in sanitation."},{"time":221079,"text":"We're kind of uncomfortable\ntalking about sanitation,"},{"time":224416,"text":"that's why I've gotten called\n\"The Poo Princess\" so much."},{"time":227142,"text":"The second reason is:"},{"time":228857,"text":"we think the problem is solved\nhere in the US."},{"time":231833,"text":"But not so."},{"time":233087,"text":"Here in the US we still get sick\nfrom drinking shit in our sewage water."},{"time":238699,"text":"Seven million people get sick every year,"},{"time":240868,"text":"900 die annually."},{"time":242663,"text":"And we're not taking a holistic\napproach to making it better."},{"time":247125,"text":"So we're not solving it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249749,"text":"Where I live in Portland, Oregon,"},{"time":251448,"text":"I can't take Echo for a swim\nduring the rainy season,"},{"time":254275,"text":"because we dump raw sewage\nsometimes into our river."},{"time":257905,"text":"Our rainwater and our sewage\ngo to the same treatment plant."},{"time":261904,"text":"Too much rain overflows into the river."},{"time":265530,"text":"And Portland is not alone here."},{"time":267569,"text":"Forty percent of municipalities self-report"},{"time":270683,"text":"dumping raw or partially treated\nsewage into our waterways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275442,"text":"The other bummer going on here\nwith our status quo"},{"time":278624,"text":"is that half of all of your poop and pee\nis going to fertilize farmland."},{"time":283819,"text":"The other half is being incinerated"},{"time":286209,"text":"or land-filled."},{"time":287447,"text":"And that's a bummer to me,"},{"time":288979,"text":"because there are amazing nutrients\nin your daily doody."},{"time":291965,"text":"It is comparable to pig manure;"},{"time":294155,"text":"we're omnivores, they're omnivores."},{"time":297240,"text":"Think of your poo and pee\nas a health smoothie for a tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300647,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305357,"text":"The other bummer going on here"},{"time":307190,"text":"is that we're quickly moving\nall the drugs we take into our waterways."},{"time":311971,"text":"The average wastewater treatment plant\ncan remove maybe half of the drugs"},{"time":316226,"text":"that come in."},{"time":317910,"text":"The other half goes\nright out the other side."},{"time":320564,"text":"Consider what a cocktail\nof pharmaceuticals --"},{"time":324044,"text":"hormones, steroids, Vicodin --"},{"time":326089,"text":"does to a fish,"},{"time":327896,"text":"to a dog,"},{"time":329142,"text":"to a child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332322,"text":"But this isn't just some problem\nthat we need to contain."},{"time":336215,"text":"If we flip this around,\nwe can create a resource"},{"time":338637,"text":"that can solve so many\nof our other problems."},{"time":341758,"text":"And I want to get you\ncomfortable with this idea,"},{"time":344162,"text":"so imagine the things I'm going\nto show you, these technologies,"},{"time":348335,"text":"and this attitude that says,"},{"time":350348,"text":"\"We're going to reuse this."},{"time":351720,"text":"Let's design to make it beautiful\" --"},{"time":353958,"text":"as advanced potty training."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355515,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356562,"text":"I think you're ready for it."},{"time":358312,"text":"I think we as a culture are ready\nfor advanced potty training."},{"time":362527,"text":"And there are three great\nreasons to enroll today."},{"time":365030,"text":"Number one:"},{"time":367094,"text":"we can fertilize our food."},{"time":369016,"text":"Each one of us is pooping\nand peeing something"},{"time":371552,"text":"that could fertilize half\nor maybe all of our food,"},{"time":374315,"text":"depending on our diet."},{"time":377060,"text":"That dark brown poo in the toilet\nis dark brown because of what?"},{"time":380359,"text":"Dead stuff, bacteria."},{"time":382249,"text":"That's carbon."},{"time":383424,"text":"And carbon, if we're getting\nthat into the soil,"},{"time":385754,"text":"is going to bind to the other minerals\nand nutrients in there."},{"time":389187,"text":"Boom! Healthier food."},{"time":391443,"text":"Voil√†! Healthier people."},{"time":394325,"text":"Chemical fertilizers by definition\ndon't have carbon in them."},{"time":399221,"text":"Imagine if we could move our animal manure\nand our human manure to our soil,"},{"time":404608,"text":"we might not need to rely\non fossil fuel-based fertilizers,"},{"time":408438,"text":"mine minerals from far away."},{"time":411395,"text":"Imagine how much energy we could save."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415230,"text":"Now, some of us are concerned"},{"time":418314,"text":"about industrial pollutants\ncontaminating this reuse cycle."},{"time":423322,"text":"That can be addressed."},{"time":425445,"text":"But we need to separate our discomfort\nabout talking about poo and pee"},{"time":430403,"text":"so we can calmly talk\nabout how we want to reuse it"},{"time":434791,"text":"and what things we don't want to reuse."},{"time":437456,"text":"And get this:"},{"time":439598,"text":"if we change our approach to sanitation,"},{"time":442417,"text":"we can start to slow down climate change."},{"time":446234,"text":"Remember that carbon in the poop?"},{"time":448800,"text":"If we can get that into our soil bank,"},{"time":451489,"text":"it's going to start to absorb\ncarbon dioxide that we put into the air."},{"time":456154,"text":"And that could help\nslow down global warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459397,"text":"I want to show you some brave souls"},{"time":461928,"text":"who've had the courage to embrace\nthis advanced potty training approach."},{"time":467028,"text":"So those folks in New Mexico --"},{"time":468743,"text":"why did they do it?"},{"time":470735,"text":"'Cause they're in a desert?\n'Cause they save money? Yeah."},{"time":473842,"text":"But more importantly,\nthey felt comfortable"},{"time":478217,"text":"seeing what was going\ndown the toilet as a resource."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481642,"text":"Here's an average house\nin Portland, Oregon."},{"time":483762,"text":"This house is special\nbecause they have a composting toilet"},{"time":486723,"text":"turning all their poo and pee,\nover time, into a soil amendment."},{"time":491547,"text":"Their wash water, their shower water,\nis going underground"},{"time":494465,"text":"to a series of mulch basins,"},{"time":497127,"text":"and then watering that orchard downhill."},{"time":500392,"text":"When they went to get this permitted,"},{"time":502901,"text":"it wasn't allowed in Oregon."},{"time":505222,"text":"But it was allowed\nin five other states nearby."},{"time":508322,"text":"That was Recode's -- my organization's --\nfirst code-change campaign."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514158,"text":"Here's a great example where\nthe Integrated Water Management approach"},{"time":518644,"text":"was the cheapest."},{"time":520108,"text":"This is three high-rise residential\nbuildings in downtown Portland,"},{"time":524728,"text":"and they're not flushing\nto the sewer system."},{"time":527332,"text":"How?"},{"time":528515,"text":"Well, their wash water\nis getting reused to flush toilets,"},{"time":532461,"text":"cool mechanical systems,"},{"time":534152,"text":"water the landscape."},{"time":536028,"text":"And then once the building\nhas thoroughly used everything --"},{"time":538906,"text":"aka, shat in it --"},{"time":540453,"text":"it's treated to highest standard\nright on-site by plants and bacteria,"},{"time":545099,"text":"and then infiltrated\ninto the groundwater right below."},{"time":549371,"text":"And all that was cheaper"},{"time":552898,"text":"than updating the surrounding\nsewer infrastructure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556553,"text":"So that's the last reason\nwe should get really excited"},{"time":559115,"text":"about doing things differently:"},{"time":560631,"text":"we can save a lot of money."},{"time":564085,"text":"This was the first permit\nof its kind in Oregon."},{"time":567597,"text":"Brave and open-minded people\nsat down and felt comfortable saying,"},{"time":572410,"text":"\"Yeah, that shit makes sense.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":573934,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":576426,"text":"\"Let's do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":577691,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578716,"text":"You know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":579891,"text":"I keep showing examples"},{"time":582064,"text":"where everyone's reusing\neverything on-site."},{"time":584246,"text":"Why?"},{"time":585421,"text":"Well, when we look at our aging\ninfrastructure -- and it is old --"},{"time":588719,"text":"and we look at the cost of updating it,"},{"time":590646,"text":"three-quarters of that cost is just\nthe pipes snaking through our city."},{"time":595666,"text":"So as we build anew, as we renovate,"},{"time":597869,"text":"it might make more sense\nto treat and reuse everything on-site."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603499,"text":"San Francisco realized that it made sense"},{"time":606094,"text":"to invest in rebates for every household"},{"time":608792,"text":"to reuse their wash water\nand their rainwater"},{"time":611349,"text":"to water the backyard,"},{"time":613006,"text":"because the amount of water they would\nsave as a community would be so big."},{"time":618261,"text":"But why were all\nthese projects so innovative?"},{"time":621434,"text":"The money piece, yeah."},{"time":623963,"text":"But more importantly,"},{"time":625638,"text":"they felt comfortable with this idea\nof advanced potty training."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629572,"text":"Imagine if we embraced\ninnovation for sanitation"},{"time":634624,"text":"the way we have for, say, solar power."},{"time":638565,"text":"Think about it -- solar power used\nto be uncommon and unaffordable."},{"time":642144,"text":"Now it's more a part\nof our web of power than ever before."},{"time":645721,"text":"And it's creating resiliency."},{"time":648130,"text":"We now have sources of power like the sun"},{"time":650988,"text":"that don't vary with our earthly dramas."},{"time":654282,"text":"What's driving all that innovation?"},{"time":657002,"text":"It's us."},{"time":658400,"text":"We're talking about energy."},{"time":660447,"text":"It's cool to talk about energy."},{"time":664032,"text":"Some folks are even talking\nabout the problems"},{"time":666207,"text":"with the limited resources\nwhere our current energy is coming from."},{"time":669397,"text":"We encourage our best and brightest\nto work on this issue --"},{"time":673485,"text":"better solar panels,\nbetter batteries, everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678099,"text":"So let's talk about where\nour drinking water is coming from,"},{"time":681233,"text":"where our poo and pee are actually going."},{"time":684344,"text":"If we can get over this discomfort\nwith this entire topic,"},{"time":689308,"text":"we could create something\nthat creates our future goldmine."},{"time":693158,"text":"Every time you flush the toilet,"},{"time":694803,"text":"I want you to think,"},{"time":696446,"text":"\"Where is my poop and pee going?"},{"time":698494,"text":"Will they be gainfully employed?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":700421,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":701697,"text":"\"Or are they going to be wreaking\nhavoc in some waterway?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":704899,"text":"If you don't know, find out."},{"time":706826,"text":"And if you don't like the answer,"},{"time":708628,"text":"figure out how you can communicate\nto those who can drive this change"},{"time":712379,"text":"that you have advanced potty training,\nthat you are ready for reuse."},{"time":716415,"text":"How all of you feel"},{"time":718866,"text":"is going to determine exactly\nhow innovative we can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722191,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723374,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}